  "prompt": "Which problems should I attempt first on TopCoder?",
  "response": "When starting out on TopCoder, it's best to ease into the platform by focusing on simpler problems first and gradually increasing the difficulty as you become more comfortable and skilled. Here are some steps to help you choose the right problems:\n\n1. **Beginner Problems:** Look for problems categorized as \"easy\" or \"beginner.\" These are designed to introduce you to the basic concepts and problem-solving techniques needed in competitive programming.\n\n2. **Recent Contests:** Participate in recent single-round matches (SRMs) as they often have a range of problems from easy to hard. Start with the easiest problem in the contest and work your way up.\n\n3. **Practice Rooms:** TopCoder has practice rooms where you can see problems sorted by difficulty and also how many users have solved them. Start with the ones that have been solved by many users, indicating they might be less challenging.\n\n4. **Algorithm Tutorials:** TopCoder offers tutorials that explain common algorithms and problem-solving techniques. Solve the example problems provided in these tutorials.\n\n5. **Use the Rating System:** TopCoder problems are rated\u2014start with problems that match your current rating or slightly below it to build confidence.\n\n6. **Past Contest Problems:** Review and attempt problems from past contests. Start with the problem rated easiest based on the number of correct submissions during the contest.\n\nRemember to analyze the solutions and explanations after attempting each problem, even when you successfully solve them. This helps in understanding more efficient or alternative methods of approaching the same problem.\n\nA structured approach like this will help you gradually improve your skills and get accustomed to the competition environment. Good luck!",
